For a new machine first install git and then from the terminal:

1) git config --global user.name "franciscovillaescusa"
2) git config --global user.email "villaescusa.francisco@gmail.com"
3) git config --global credential.helper cache
4) git init
5) git remote add origin https://github.com/franciscovillaescusa/Fcodes.git
6) git pull origin master


For submit changes to the server:

1) git status
2) To see changes in modified files: git diff filename
1) git add borrar.py or git add --all
2) git commit -m "change in library"
3) git push origin master


For receive the changes from the server:

1) git pull origin master


If you just want to pull the changes then:

1) git fetch --all
2) git reset origin/master --soft
3) In case the step 2) fails use: git reset origin/master --hard